<h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid When Hiring</h2>
<p>The most common mistake homeowners make is hiring based on the lowest bid alone. This often leads to cut corners, subpar materials, and unexpected costs down the line.<br/><br/>Another critical error is failing to get a detailed, written contract before any work begins or money changes hands. This document is your primary protection.<br/><br/>Finally, avoid "scope creep"—making constant changes without formal change orders, which can quickly derail your budget and timeline.</p>

